## Real-world verdict

**InboxZero wins on market reality.**

Why:
- Every company with more than 2 support people feels this pain weekly — duplicate replies, lost tickets, slow response → angry customers → lost revenue. Dollars on the line, not comfort.
- Budget already exists. Teams pay $50–100/seat for Zendesk / Intercom today; a self-hosted or cheaper alternative at $5–10/seat has an obvious market.
- Clear buyer, short sales cycle — support lead or founder signs off in a single call.
- Switching cost from Gmail labels is low, unlike leaving Jira or Linear.

**DeskPilot second** — strong pain, smaller market, longer sales cycle (office managers, procurement). Good niche but fewer buyers.

**TaskFlow last as a product** — fighting Linear, Jira, Trello, Asana, ClickUp, Monday, Notion. Commoditized, low urgency, huge switching cost. Good portfolio piece, bad business.

